    CLIMATE SCIENCE OLYMPIAD 2023 School Qualifying Round on March 1, 2023

    by Mary Joy Villamora - Friday, 17 February 2023, 7:54 AM

    The student competition to find solutions to climate change. Open to all interested G11 scholars.

    1. How It Works

    Please watch this trailer for Climate Science Olympiad 2023:

      2. Timeline of all Rounds

       

      3. School Qualifying Round (Campus-based Screening)

      A 25-minute online quiz will be done in sync for all interested G11 scholars on March 1, 2023 at 3:00 PM and will serve as a qualifying round at PSHS-CVisC Level.  Each person can participate up to 3 times. All participants will receive a certificate. 

      In preparation for this round, the interested participants will be given access to Climate Science Courses and activities.  and Before the actual test, a mock exam using the CS Quiz app will be conducted.

      4. Quarter Finals (Best 10% globally)

      The best 10% of all qualifier attempts advance to the Quarter Finals. Quarter Finals follow the same quick-question format as Qualifying Round (25-minute online quiz).

      5. Semi-Finals

      In the Semi-Finals, the partcipants choose one of three problem statements to respond to. To help them prepare, the partcipants are told the topics 10 days before the event, but the exact problem statement is only revealed at the start of the actual qualifier event. Then they have 3 hours to research and write essay responses to questions related to the problem statement. ClimateScience.org will score each team's solution.

      6. Finals (Top 100 globally)

      Format: Finalists receive a complex global problem and they have to write a 3000 word proposal aiming to solve the problem at hand. They then present their solution in a 20 minute presentation judged by world-leading scientists, innovators and policy-makers.

      Certificate: Every Finalist is awarded a Bronze Medal certificate, the top 20 and top 10 will be awarded a Silver and Gold Medal certificate, respectively.

      Awards: The top 10 teams will be awarded with a sponsored trip to Dubai, UAE during United Nations Climate Summit, COP28.


      IF YOU ARE INTERESTED TO JOIN THE SCHOOL QUALIFYING ROUND, PLEASE EMAIL YOUR PARENT'S CONSENT to mmvillamora@cvisc.pshs.edu.ph ON OR BEFORE FRIDAY, FEBRUARY 24, 2023.

      Thank you!

      Dorm Arrival of Gr. 8-10 Scholars for 2nd Quarter In-Person Classes

      by Kenneth Balili - Wednesday, 2 November 2022, 12:10 PM

      Hello gr. 8-10 scholars!

      I guess you are excited to come to the campus for your in-person classes in the second quarter. We are excited to see you on campus as well. As scheduled in our school calendar and posted on our FB page, your in-person classes will begin on November 9 (Wednesday). Hence, you are expected to arrive on campus on November 7-8 (Monday-Tuesday). However, if you wish to arrive earlier than that, you will be required to secure the approval of our Campus Director through a written request (may be emailed to ocd@cvisc.pshs.edu.ph). Approved early arrival may be made on November 6 (Sunday) only. We cannot accommodate dormers yet on November 5 (Saturday) because of the general cleaning and disinfection that will be conducted, especially in the dormitories. I hope that this clarifies your concern about dorm arrival. Make sure to undergo thorough health screening in the designated area before entering the dormitories.

      Have a safe trip in traveling to the campus. See you!
